I am pretty busy. It's hectic.

64
00:04:42,682 --> 00:04:44,284
This year was really

65
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:49,555
a productive year. That's the only word
that can describe it.

66
00:04:51,724 --> 00:04:52,592
{\an8}Ready...

67
00:04:52,659 --> 00:04:53,860
{\an8}JULY 2018 COMMERCIAL FILMING

68
00:04:53,926 --> 00:04:55,628
{\an8}<i>Even when his schedule is packed,</i>

69
00:04:55,895 --> 00:04:59,332
{\an8}<i>Hirano's genuine personality shows
through his innocent smile.</i>

70
00:05:00,199 --> 00:05:03,369
<i>He would also say things
you wouldn't expect from an idol.</i>

71
00:05:05,805 --> 00:05:08,675
Look at how I walk.
I look like an old man.

72
00:05:11,778 --> 00:05:14,347
An idol shouldn't be
walking like this, actually.

73
00:05:14,414 --> 00:05:18,017
I should be walking like this.

74
00:05:19,719 --> 00:05:23,289
<i>Hirano decided to become an idol
in elementary school.</i>

75
00:05:24,190 --> 00:05:27,327
<i>He was able to work hard
because he wanted to help his mother.</i>

76
00:05:28,628 --> 00:05:30,997
I was raised by a single mother.

77
00:05:31,064 --> 00:05:32,832
My mother almost died once.

78
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:38,204
I didn't want to make my mother sad,

79
00:05:39,205 --> 00:05:42,375
so I felt like I had to
work hard at my job.

80
00:05:45,311 --> 00:05:46,245
{\an8}There's nothing here.

81
00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:50,683
{\an8}<i>What left an impression was
what he said in his hometown of Nagoya.</i>

82
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,385
{\an8}SEPTEMBER 2018 NAGOYA

83
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:55,355
Was there anything you wanted to be
other than an idol?

84
00:05:56,055 --> 00:05:57,357
So many things.

85
00:05:57,657 --> 00:06:01,694
I like protecting people.

86
00:06:02,929 --> 00:06:07,500
I wanted to go to
disaster areas and help out,

87
00:06:08,901 --> 00:06:12,271
but I was told that...

88
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:16,943
even if I can't physically help them

89
00:06:17,009 --> 00:06:18,911
by removing debris and whatnot,

90
00:06:19,345 --> 00:06:25,318
people who see us on TV,
or in magazines, or at concerts

91
00:06:26,252 --> 00:06:30,056
can be emotionally uplifted
and motivated to live another day.

92
00:06:31,357 --> 00:06:35,261
That's why, at the end of concerts,
I often say, "Don't die."

93
00:06:35,695 --> 00:06:38,798
Even if we couldn't make eye contact
at the concert,

94
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:42,168
I want everyone who is watching me
and who is connected with me

95
00:06:42,402 --> 00:06:45,805
to stay alive. I really do.

96
00:06:45,872 --> 00:06:49,809
The reason I'm continuing this job,
is because I want to

97
00:06:51,177 --> 00:06:54,714
lift everyone's spirits.

98
00:06:56,716 --> 00:06:58,518
All right.

99
00:06:58,584 --> 00:06:59,952
<i>How did Hirano deal with</i>

100
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:03,556
<i>the massive pressure that weighed down</i>

101
00:07:03,623 --> 00:07:05,324
<i>on him this past year?</i>

102
00:07:05,391 --> 00:07:07,994
One, two, one, two.

103
00:07:08,060 --> 00:07:09,896
<i>His answer was unique.</i>

104
00:07:10,797 --> 00:07:11,631
Let's go!

105
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:17,937
Pressure... I didn't really feel it.

106
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:20,740
I guess I should have felt the pressure.

107
00:07:20,807 --> 00:07:22,341
The agency would want me to.

108
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:26,179
Before a big performance,
they would tell me,

109
00:07:26,245 --> 00:07:28,714
"We're counting on you!" pretty often.

110
00:07:29,348 --> 00:07:31,951
Even during the shows,
they're constantly telling me,

111
00:07:32,351 --> 00:07:33,786
"Please make it work"

112
00:07:34,487 --> 00:07:36,589
and "We're counting on you to do this."

113
00:07:37,423 --> 00:07:38,724
I get that a lot.

114
00:07:40,326 --> 00:07:42,829
But I don't want to let those words

115
00:07:43,896 --> 00:07:45,565
get me nervous.

116
00:07:46,566 --> 00:07:50,503
I brush it off. I dodge their words.

117
00:07:52,038 --> 00:07:53,806
I make sure that I'm putting in

118
00:07:55,074 --> 00:07:57,977
one hundred percent, though.

119
00:08:05,284 --> 00:08:09,422
<i>In the show,
the one who played a fighting soldier</i>

120
00:08:13,292 --> 00:08:14,660
{\an8}<i>was Yuta Jinguji.</i>

121
00:08:16,562 --> 00:08:20,800
{\an8}<i>For him, this year was
a crucial turning point in his life.</i>

122
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:29,308
{\an8}TOYOKAWA INARI TOKYO BETSUIN
MOTOAKASAKA, TOKYO

123
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:32,111
{\an8}<i>Jinguji opened up about
his deepest thoughts</i>

124
00:08:32,678 --> 00:08:35,248
{\an8}<i>when we visited a certain temple.</i>

125
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:41,487
That was really shocking for me.
I was 18 at the time.

126
00:08:43,656 --> 00:08:46,025
That was the toughest time of my life.

127
00:08:46,692 --> 00:08:47,960
When we didn't get offers.

128
00:08:49,629 --> 00:08:52,598
If there's no work coming in
even though I'm willing,

129
00:08:53,499 --> 00:08:56,202
I thought for a second,
that maybe I should quit.

130
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:59,138
{\an8}MYOJO LIVE! 2015 SUMMER CONCERT ISSUE

131
00:08:59,205 --> 00:09:04,176
{\an8}<i>The six of them formed a unit together
for the first time in 2015,</i>

132
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:06,779
{\an8}<i>but from the following year,</i>

133
00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:10,049
{\an8}<i>they broke up into two units of three.</i>

134
00:09:12,985 --> 00:09:16,389
{\an8}<i>One unit caught people's
attention immediately.</i>

135
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:20,426
{\an8}<i>However, the unit Jinguji was in</i>

136
00:09:20,793 --> 00:09:22,194
{\an8}<i>was left in the shadows.</i>

137
00:09:22,595 --> 00:09:25,998
{\an8}<i>Without work,
they were left feeling frustrated.</i>

138
00:09:26,065 --> 00:09:28,701
{\an8}MYOJO LIVE! 2017 SUMMER CONCERT ISSUE

139
00:09:29,101 --> 00:09:30,169
{\an8}JUNE 2018 MOVIE FILMING

140
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:34,240
{\an8}<i>That is why, when it was decided that
the six of them were going to debut,</i>

141
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:37,476
<i>he swore to do anything it took.</i>

142
00:09:40,479 --> 00:09:41,314
Cut.

143
00:09:45,551 --> 00:09:47,053
<i>When he was filming a movie,</i>

144
00:09:47,486 --> 00:09:51,290
<i>he was repeatedly told to retake
one scene for over two hours.</i>

145
00:09:54,627 --> 00:09:58,130
<i>What has supported Jinguji
during this past year?</i>

146
00:09:59,732 --> 00:10:01,567
Since we were the ones who told

147
00:10:01,968 --> 00:10:06,072
Mr. Johnny that we wanted to debut,

148
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:08,774
of course I felt
the responsibility and pressure.

149
00:10:09,175 --> 00:10:10,309
What if...

150
00:10:11,077 --> 00:10:13,579
What if our CDs don't sell?

151
00:10:14,647 --> 00:10:17,116
What if we don't live up
to their expectations?

152
00:10:18,084 --> 00:10:19,619
I did worry about that.

153
00:10:20,786 --> 00:10:22,188
Mr. Johnny created us,

154
00:10:23,923 --> 00:10:27,693
so I felt the pressure
of not wanting to put him to shame.

155
00:10:28,828 --> 00:10:31,197
But now, those thoughts don't even

156
00:10:31,697 --> 00:10:34,767
cross my mind anymore, because our fans

157
00:10:34,834 --> 00:10:37,937
are so supportive of us.

158
00:10:38,004 --> 00:10:41,607
Now, all I can think about
is how I can give back.

159
00:10:41,941 --> 00:10:43,609
I want to give back to them.

160
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:51,817
<i>Supporting the group
with similar feelings to Jinguji</i>

161
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:57,857
{\an8}<i>were the two youngest members,
Ren Nagase</i>

162
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:01,127
{\an8}<i>and Kaito Takahashi.</i>

163
00:11:02,995 --> 00:11:06,465
{\an8}<i>These two met up with their mentors
who gave them courage.</i>

164
00:11:10,302 --> 00:11:11,504
{\an8}SEPTEMBER 2018 OSAKA

165
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:14,340
{\an8}<i>During his brief time off,
Nagase headed toward Osaka,</i>

166
00:11:15,141 --> 00:11:18,210
<i>where he spent
his middle and high school years.</i>

167
00:11:19,779 --> 00:11:22,314
{\an8}This is also where I joined Johnny's,

168
00:11:22,682 --> 00:11:27,319
{\an8}so I see this city as my birthplace
as a Johnny's member.

169
00:11:28,054 --> 00:11:32,591
My personality
was shaped here in Osaka as well.

170
00:11:36,629 --> 00:11:37,496
There he is.

171
00:11:37,797 --> 00:11:39,098
{\an8}Long time no see.

172
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:40,366
{\an8}There he is.

173
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:44,970
{\an8}<i>He met up with his homeroom teacher
from middle school, Mr. Ukon.</i>

174
00:11:47,807 --> 00:11:50,076
<i>When Nagase was unsure about his future,</i>

175
00:11:50,776 --> 00:11:52,511
<i>he was there to give encouragement.</i>

176
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:56,549
He was worrying about it
more than anyone else.

177
00:11:56,615 --> 00:11:59,351
You wanted to either study
or work in the entertainment industry.

178
00:11:59,418 --> 00:12:02,154
Because my grades were pretty good.

179
00:12:02,588 --> 00:12:04,223
That's right. You weren't sure.

180
00:12:04,290 --> 00:12:05,558
I thought it would be a waste.

181
00:12:05,891 --> 00:12:07,093
I thought that if I chose

182
00:12:07,159 --> 00:12:11,964
while I was young,
I'd still have time to start over again.

183
00:12:12,832 --> 00:12:13,933
You've grown up so much.

184
00:12:13,999 --> 00:12:14,867
It's the fans.

185
00:12:15,668 --> 00:12:17,970
Seriously, it's all thanks to them.

186
00:12:18,204 --> 00:12:19,138
I mean...

187
00:12:20,172 --> 00:12:24,143
When the fans cheer for us
during our concerts,

188
00:12:24,210 --> 00:12:26,812
-it honestly feels really great.
-I see.

189
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:28,781
It feels better than you'd imagine.

190
00:12:28,848 --> 00:12:31,350
You came so close, remember?

191
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:34,687
And during your performance,
you waved at me.

192
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:37,690
When I called out your name,
you waved at me.

193
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:40,626
Then the fans around me
started screaming,

194
00:12:41,460 --> 00:12:43,863
but inside, I was thinking,
"No, he's waving at me!"

195
00:12:49,502 --> 00:12:52,438
<i>There are people who are
watching over him from afar.</i>

196
00:12:55,341 --> 00:12:57,877
{\an8}<i>Meanwhile, in a previous interview,</i>

197
00:12:58,210 --> 00:12:59,812
{\an8}<i>Takahashi had said this...</i>

198
00:13:00,646 --> 00:13:03,182
I just don't have a lot of
self-confidence.

199
00:13:03,249 --> 00:13:04,283
That's how I am.

200
00:13:04,784 --> 00:13:06,519
It was decided in January.

201
00:13:06,886 --> 00:13:09,889
I was worried if I could
handle all the pressure.

202
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:12,191
Tears just began to stream down.

203
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:15,094
{\an8}Long time no see.

204
00:13:15,528 --> 00:13:18,364
{\an8}<i>One person who gave Takahashi courage</i>

205
00:13:18,898 --> 00:13:22,401
{\an8}<i>was his high school teacher, Mr. Nakao.</i>

206
00:13:22,468 --> 00:13:23,569
{\an8}TEACHER TADASHI NAKAO

207
00:13:23,936 --> 00:13:26,138
He always knew when I was tired.

208
00:13:26,705 --> 00:13:28,974
He could tell if I was up late at night.

209
00:13:29,575 --> 00:13:32,845
Every day, I would talk to him
about my work,

210
00:13:32,912 --> 00:13:35,481
as if I was reporting to him.

211
00:13:35,548 --> 00:13:39,552
That's right. You did that a lot.
You would tell me your plans for the day.

212
00:13:39,618 --> 00:13:41,187
And what I did that day.

213
00:13:43,189 --> 00:13:47,960
<i>What made Takahashi the happiest
was a gift from his teacher.</i>

214
00:13:50,229 --> 00:13:51,230
Wow!

215
00:13:51,297 --> 00:13:52,531
{\an8}LAUGHTER, APPRECIATION

216
00:13:52,598 --> 00:13:54,266
{\an8}I'm so happy.

217
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,734
Oh, wow!

218
00:13:56,535 --> 00:13:57,937
One second.

219
00:13:58,003 --> 00:14:03,075
When I went to your place,
you gave me one.

220
00:14:04,543 --> 00:14:07,713
I brought it. Now I have a complete set.

221
00:14:07,780 --> 00:14:09,014
{\an8}HARD WORK PAYS OFF
KAITO TAKAHASHI

222
00:14:09,715 --> 00:14:12,451
{\an8}They have a magical power.
It makes me realize that

223
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:14,053
{\an8}it's important for me
to always be smiling.

224
00:14:14,119 --> 00:14:15,321
That's what an idol is to me.

225
00:14:17,556 --> 00:14:22,161
<i>With those words ingrained in his heart,
how did he survive this past year?</i>

226
00:14:24,830 --> 00:14:27,700
Days off? Ever since I started
performing at the theater

227
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:32,037
I haven't had a single day off.
Yeah, not a single day.

228
00:14:32,605 --> 00:14:37,209
But I feel like I can be myself
when I'm working

229
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,645
more than when I'm not.

230
00:14:40,446 --> 00:14:43,315
I want to spend more time
with the other members.

231
00:14:44,516 --> 00:14:48,053
I want to talk more with the staff too.

232
00:14:49,321 --> 00:14:52,858
<i>Time has turned the young boy
who was constantly crying</i>

233
00:14:52,925 --> 00:14:54,827
<i>into someone so dependable.</i>

234
00:14:59,031 --> 00:15:00,499
<i>Nagase, on the other hand...</i>

235
00:15:03,335 --> 00:15:05,271
It went by so fast.

236
